trans-unit.source: Similar to FusedResizeAndPadConv2d, this op allows for an optimized implementation where the spatial padding transformation stage is fused with the im2col lookup, but in this case without the bilinear filtering required for resizing. Fusing the padding prevents the need to write out the intermediate results as whole tensors, reducing memory pressure, and we can get some latency gains by merging the transformation calculations. The data_format attribute for Conv2D isn't supported by this op, and 'NHWC' order is used instead. Internally this op uses a single per-graph scratch buffer, which means that it will block if multiple versions are being run in parallel. This is because this operator is primarily an optimization to minimize memory usage.
trans-unit.target: 与FusedResizeAndPadConv2d类似,这个操作允许一个优化的实现,其中空间填充变换阶段与im2col查找融合,但在这种情况下,没有调整大小所需的双线性过滤。融合填充可以避免将中间结果写成整数,减少内存压力,而且我们可以通过合并变换计算获得一些延迟收益。这个操作不支持Conv2D的data_format属性,而是使用'NHWC'顺序。在内部,这个运算符使用了一个单一的每图抓取缓冲区,这意味着如果多个版本被并行运行,它将被阻塞。这是因为这个操作符主要是为了最小化内存使用而进行的优化。
